attributes.name: employeeNumber
attributes.description:
Numeric or alphanumeric identifier assigned 
to a person, typically based on order of hire or association with an 
organization.

attributes.name: costCenter
attributes.description: Identifies the name of a cost center.

attributes.name: organization
attributes.description: Identifies the name of an organization.

attributes.name: division
attributes.description: Identifies the name of a division.

attributes.name: department
attributes.description: Identifies the name of a department.

attributes.name: manager
attributes.description:
The User's manager.  A complex type that 
optionally allows service providers to represent organizational 
hierarchy by referencing the 'id' attribute of another User.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description:
The id of the SCIM resource representing 
the User's manager.  REQUIRED.

subAttributes.name: $ref
subAttributes.description:
The URI of the SCIM resource 
representing the User's manager.  REQUIRED.

subAttributes.name: displayName
subAttributes.description:
The displayName of the User's manager. 
OPTIONAL and READ-ONLY.

attributes.name: userName
attributes.description:
Unique identifier for the User, typically 
used by the user to directly authenticate to the service provider. 
Each User MUST include a non-empty userName value.  This identifier 
MUST be unique across the service provider's entire set of Users. 
REQUIRED.

attributes.name: name
attributes.description:
The components of the user's real name. 
Providers MAY return just the full name as a single string in the 
formatted sub-attribute, or they MAY return just the individual 
component attributes using the other sub-attributes, or they MAY 
return both.  If both variants are returned, they SHOULD be 
describing the same name, with the formatted name indicating how the 
component attributes should be combined.

subAttributes.name: formatted
subAttributes.description:
The full name, including all middle 
names, titles, and suffixes as appropriate, formatted for display 
(e.g., 'Ms. Barbara J Jensen, III').

subAttributes.name: familyName
subAttributes.description:
The family name of the User, or 
last name in most Western languages (e.g., 'Jensen' given the full 
name 'Ms. Barbara J Jensen, III').

subAttributes.name: givenName
subAttributes.description:
The given name of the User, or 
first name in most Western languages (e.g., 'Barbara' given the 
full name 'Ms. Barbara J Jensen, III').

subAttributes.name: middleName
subAttributes.description:
The middle name(s) of the User 
(e.g., 'Jane' given the full name 'Ms. Barbara J Jensen, III').

subAttributes.name: honorificPrefix
subAttributes.description:
The honorific prefix(es) of the User, or 
title in most Western languages (e.g., 'Ms.' given the full name 
'Ms. Barbara J Jensen, III').

subAttributes.name: honorificSuffix
subAttributes.description:
The honorific suffix(es) of the User, or 
suffix in most Western languages (e.g., 'III' given the full name 
'Ms. Barbara J Jensen, III').

attributes.name: displayName
attributes.description:
The name of the User, suitable for display 
to end-users.  The name SHOULD be the full name of the User being 
described, if known.

attributes.name: nickName
attributes.description:
The casual way to address the user in real 
life, e.g., 'Bob' or 'Bobby' instead of 'Robert'.  This attribute 
SHOULD NOT be used to represent a User's username (e.g., 'bjensen' or 
'mpepperidge').

attributes.name: profileUrl
attributes.description:
A fully qualified URL pointing to a page 
representing the User's online profile.

attributes.name: title
attributes.description:
The user's title, such as 
"Vice President."

attributes.name: userType
attributes.description:
Used to identify the relationship between 
the organization and the user.  Typical values used might be 
'Contractor', 'Employee', 'Intern', 'Temp', 'External', and 
'Unknown', but any value may be used.

attributes.name: preferredLanguage
attributes.description:
Indicates the User's preferred written or 
spoken language.  Generally used for selecting a localized user 
interface; e.g., 'en_US' specifies the language English and country 
US.

attributes.name: locale
attributes.description:
Used to indicate the User's default location 
for purposes of localizing items such as currency, date time format, or 
numerical representations.

attributes.name: timezone
attributes.description:
The User's time zone in the 'Olson' time zone 
database format, e.g., 'America/Los_Angeles'.

attributes.name: active
attributes.description:
A Boolean value indicating the User's 
administrative status.

attributes.name: password
attributes.description:
The User's cleartext password.  This 
attribute is intended to be used as a means to specify an initial 
password when creating a new User or to reset an existing User's 
password.

attributes.name: emails
attributes.description:
Email addresses for the user.  The value 
SHOULD be canonicalized by the service provider, e.g., 
'bjensen@example.com' instead of 'bjensen@EXAMPLE.COM'. 
Canonical type values of 'work', 'home', and 'other'.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description:
Email addresses for the user.  The value 
SHOULD be canonicalized by the service provider, e.g., 
'bjensen@example.com' instead of 'bjensen@EXAMPLE.COM'. 
Canonical type values of 'work', 'home', and 'other'.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description:
A human-readable name, primarily used 
for display purposes.  READ-ONLY.

subAttributes.name: type
subAttributes.description:
A label indicating the attribute's 
function, e.g., 'work' or 'home'.

subAttributes.name: primary
subAttributes.description:
A Boolean value indicating the 'primary' 
or preferred attribute value for this attribute, e.g., the preferred 
mailing address or primary email address.  The primary attribute 
value 'true' MUST appear no more than once.

attributes.name: phoneNumbers
attributes.description:
Phone numbers for the User.  The value 
SHOULD be canonicalized by the service provider according to the 
format specified in RFC 3966, e.g., 'tel:+1-201-555-0123'. 
Canonical type values of 'work', 'home', 'mobile', 'fax', 'pager', 
and 'other'.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: Phone number of the User.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description:
A human-readable name, primarily used 
for display purposes.  READ-ONLY.

subAttributes.name: type
subAttributes.description:
A label indicating the attribute's 
function, e.g., 'work', 'home', 'mobile'.

subAttributes.name: primary
subAttributes.description:
A Boolean value indicating the 'primary' 
or preferred attribute value for this attribute, e.g., the preferred 
phone number or primary phone number.  The primary attribute value 
'true' MUST appear no more than once.

attributes.name: ims
attributes.description: Instant messaging addresses for the User.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: Instant messaging address for the User.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description:
A human-readable name, primarily used 
for display purposes.  READ-ONLY.

subAttributes.name: type
subAttributes.description:
A label indicating the attribute's 
function, e.g., 'aim', 'gtalk', 'xmpp'.

subAttributes.name: primary
subAttributes.description:
A Boolean value indicating the 'primary' 
or preferred attribute value for this attribute, e.g., the preferred 
messenger or primary messenger.  The primary attribute value 'true' 
MUST appear no more than once.

attributes.name: photos
attributes.description: URLs of photos of the User.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: URL of a photo of the User.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description:
A human-readable name, primarily used 
for display purposes.  READ-ONLY.

subAttributes.name: type
subAttributes.description:
A label indicating the attribute's 
function, i.e., 'photo' or 'thumbnail'.

subAttributes.name: primary
subAttributes.description:
A Boolean value indicating the 'primary' 
or preferred attribute value for this attribute, e.g., the preferred 
photo or thumbnail.  The primary attribute value 'true' MUST appear 
no more than once.

attributes.name: addresses
attributes.description:
A physical mailing address for this User. 
Canonical type values of 'work', 'home', and 'other'.  This attribute 
is a complex type with the following sub-attributes.

subAttributes.name: formatted
subAttributes.description:
The full mailing address, formatted for 
display or use with a mailing label.  This attribute MAY contain 
newlines.

subAttributes.name: streetAddress
subAttributes.description:
The full street address component, 
which may include house number, street name, P.O. box, and multi-line 
extended street address information.  This attribute MAY contain 
newlines.

subAttributes.name: locality
subAttributes.description: The city or locality component.

subAttributes.name: region
subAttributes.description: The state or region component.

subAttributes.name: postalCode
subAttributes.description: The zip code or postal code component.

subAttributes.name: country
subAttributes.description: The country name component.

subAttributes.name: type
subAttributes.description:
A label indicating the attribute's 
function, e.g., 'work' or 'home'.

attributes.name: groups
attributes.description:
A list of groups to which the user belongs, 
either through direct membership, through nested groups, or 
dynamically calculated.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: The identifier of the User's group.

subAttributes.name: $ref
subAttributes.description:
The URI of the corresponding 'Group' 
resource to which the user belongs.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description:
A human-readable name, primarily used 
for display purposes.  READ-ONLY.

subAttributes.name: type
subAttributes.description:
A label indicating the attribute's 
function, e.g., 'direct' or 'indirect'.

attributes.name: entitlements
attributes.description:
A list of entitlements for the User that 
represent a thing the User has.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: The value of an entitlement.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description:
A human-readable name, primarily used 
for display purposes.  READ-ONLY.

subAttributes.name: type
subAttributes.description:
A label indicating the attribute's 
function.

subAttributes.name: primary
subAttributes.description:
A Boolean value indicating the 'primary' 
or preferred attribute value for this attribute.  The primary 
attribute value 'true' MUST appear no more than once.

attributes.name: roles
attributes.description:
A list of roles for the User that 
collectively represent who the User is, e.g., 'Student', 'Faculty'.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: The value of a role.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description:
A human-readable name, primarily used 
for display purposes.  READ-ONLY.

subAttributes.name: type
subAttributes.description:
A label indicating the attribute's 
function.

subAttributes.name: primary
subAttributes.description:
A Boolean value indicating the 'primary' 
or preferred attribute value for this attribute.  The primary 
attribute value 'true' MUST appear no more than once.

attributes.name: x509Certificates
attributes.description: A list of certificates issued to the User.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: The value of an X.509 certificate.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description:
A human-readable name, primarily used 
for display purposes.  READ-ONLY.

subAttributes.name: type
subAttributes.description:
A label indicating the attribute's 
function.

subAttributes.name: primary
subAttributes.description:
A Boolean value indicating the 'primary' 
or preferred attribute value for this attribute.  The primary 
attribute value 'true' MUST appear no more than once.

attributes.name: displayName
attributes.description:
A human-readable name for the Group. 
REQUIRED.

attributes.name: members
attributes.description: A list of members of the Group.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: Identifier of the member of this Group.

subAttributes.name: $ref
subAttributes.description:
The URI corresponding to a SCIM resource 
that is a member of this Group.

subAttributes.name: type
subAttributes.description:
A label indicating the type of resource, 
e.g., 'User' or 'Group'.

Resources.name: Privileged Data
Resources.description:
Privileged data is secret information that is protected by the PAM
    system (eg - a credential, an SSH key, etc...).  Privileged data MAY be stored
    inside of a Container, but does not have to be.

attributes.name: id
attributes.description: The unique identifier of the PrivilegedData.

attributes.name: name
attributes.description:
A descriptive name for this piece of PrivilegedData.
        For example, root@mylinuxhost

attributes.name: description
attributes.description: A description for this piece of PrivilegedData.

attributes.name: type
attributes.description:
The type of PrivilegedData.  The value will be dependent on what
        is supported by the PAM system.  Examples include 'credential', 'ssh key',
        'file', etc...

Resources.name: Container Permission
Resources.description: ACL information that is attached to a container.

attributes.name: id
attributes.description: The unique identifier of the ContainerPermission.

attributes.name: container
attributes.description: The container that these permissions apply to. REQUIRED

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: The ID of the container that these permissions apply to.

subAttributes.name: $ref
subAttributes.description: A URI reference to the container that these permissions apply to.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description: The display name of the container

subAttributes.name: name
subAttributes.description: The name of the container

attributes.name: user
attributes.description:
The User that these permissions apply to.  Either this or group
        is required.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: The ID of the user that these permissions apply to.

subAttributes.name: $ref
subAttributes.description: A URI reference to the user that these permissions apply to.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description: The display name of the user

attributes.name: group
attributes.description:
The Group that these permissions apply to.  Either this or user
        is required.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: The ID of the group that these permissions apply to.

subAttributes.name: $ref
subAttributes.description: A URI reference to the group that these permissions apply to.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description: The display name of the group

attributes.name: rights
attributes.description: The rights that the user or group has on this container.

Resources.name: Container
Resources.description:
A Container is a logical grouping of privileged data (credentials,
		etc...) that can be used for organizational or operational purposes.

attributes.name: id
attributes.description: The unique identifier of the Container

attributes.name: name
attributes.description: The name of the container.

attributes.name: displayName
attributes.description:
The display name of the container.  This is optional.  If null,
			the name will be used as the display name.

attributes.name: description
attributes.description: The description of the container.

attributes.name: type
attributes.description:
The type of container (eg - management set or account store).
			This is optional if the PAM system does not support multiple types of
			containers.

attributes.name: owner
attributes.description: The user that owns this container.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: The ID of the user that owns this container

subAttributes.name: $ref
subAttributes.description: A URI reference to the user that owns this container.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description: The display name of the user that owns this container

attributes.name: privilegedData
attributes.description: The privileged data that resides in this container.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: The ID of the privileged data.

subAttributes.name: $ref
subAttributes.description: A URI reference to the PrivilegedData

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description: The displayable value of the PrivilegedData

subAttributes.name: type
subAttributes.description: The type of the PrivilegedData.

Resources.name: Privileged Data Permission
Resources.description: ACL information that is attached to privileged data.

attributes.name: id
attributes.description: The unique identifier of the PrivilegedDataPermission.

attributes.name: privilegedData
attributes.description: The PrivilegedData that these permissions apply to. REQUIRED

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: The ID of the PrivilegedData that these permissions apply to.

subAttributes.name: $ref
subAttributes.description:
A URI reference to the PrivilegedData that these permissions
            apply to.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description: The display value of the PrivilegedData

attributes.name: user
attributes.description:
The User that these permissions apply to.  Either this or group
        is required.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: The ID of the user that these permissions apply to.

subAttributes.name: $ref
subAttributes.description: A URI reference to the user that these permissions apply to.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description: The display name of the user

attributes.name: group
attributes.description:
The Group that these permissions apply to.  Either this or user
        is required.

subAttributes.name: value
subAttributes.description: The ID of the group that these permissions apply to.

subAttributes.name: $ref
subAttributes.description: A URI reference to the group that these permissions apply to.

subAttributes.name: display
subAttributes.description: The display name of the group

attributes.name: rights
attributes.description: The rights that the user or group has on this privileged data.
